A partnership between Mastercard Foundation Young Africa Works and Babban Gona in Nigeria seeks to empower individuals in the agricultural value chain and support the acceleration of agribusinesses. In 2020 alone, the partnership successfully created 82,000 jobs, of which 70% were for youth and 33% for women. The partnership estimates 560,000 individuals, predominantly youth and women, will have access to dignified and fulfilling work by 2022. Learn more.  Find out more about Mastercard Foundation in Africa.